Bitbucket wiki supports Pygments syntax.

It seems only it works at the top level, unfortunately.

I hope that Pygments blocks can be indented into lists, same as GitHub wiki.

Sample code:

{code}
# header 1

## header 1.1

1. Description 1

{code}

Some code 1

{code}
1. Description 2

{code}

Some code 2

{code}
{code}

Instead of getting diff from https://bitbucket.org/piotrkarbowski/better-initramfs/commits/ddb1076700e6317a29998170d546ea3a95bc8430/raw/ what I got is

{code}
#!
<GitDiff ddb1076700e6:853f8388b71a>

{code}

Have spent 5+ minutes watching Chrome refresh the page with &#x27;Creating Repository&#x27;

Opened Safari to see if it was a browser specific issue, in the dashboard, clicked the link that says the repo was created, same refresh after refresh behavior.

Used Safari to create an additional new repo, same effect.

Steps to reproduce

# Create a milestone such as &#x27;X & Y&#x27;
# Create an issue with &#x27;X & Y&#x27; as the milestone
# Go to the issue list, click on &#x27;X & Y&#x27;
# Always showing zero issues.
